Git = A version-control tool that tracks changes in a project.
GitHub = An online platform that stores Git repositories and enables collaboration
Repository = A project folder that Git tracks.
Why GitHub? = To collaborate, track changes, review work, and maintain project history.
## What I Learned Today
- Git is a Version Control System.
- GitHub stores Git repositories online.
- A Repository is a Git-tracked project.
- A Commit is a saved snapshot of the project.
